==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Centipede
<hw>Cen"ti*pede</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>centipeda</ets>; <ets>centum</ets> a hundred + <ets>pes</ets>,
<ets>pedis</ets>, foot: cf. F. <ets>centip⟦egrave⟧de</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A species of the <class>Myriapoda</class>; esp.
the large, flattened, venomous kinds of the order <ord>Chilopoda</ord>,
found in tropical climates. they are many-jointed, and have a great
number of feet.</def> <altsp>[Formerly also <grk>chi`lioi</grk>
<asp>centiped</asp> (<?/).]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Centistere</ent>⟦br⟧
